INFO:argostranslate.utils:('value_hypotheses:', [('Antibiotics are a class of antimicrobials used to treat bacterial infections by killing bacteria or suppressing their growth. The mechanism of action of different groups of antibiotics is significantly different: penicillins and cephalosporins disrupt the synthesis of the cell wall of bacteria, aminoglycosides inhibit protein synthesis at the ribosome level, and fluoroquinolones inhibit enzymes necessary for DNA replication. The misuse of antibiotics has led to the emergence and spread of resistant strains of bacteria, a problem recognized by the WHO as one of the serious threats to global health.', -12.061860799789429)])
INFO:argostranslate.utils:('translated_paragraphs:', [[('Antibiotics are a class of antimicrobials used to treat bacterial infections by killing bacteria or suppressing their growth. The mechanism of action of different groups of antibiotics is significantly different: penicillins and cephalosporins disrupt the synthesis of the cell wall of bacteria, aminoglycosides inhibit protein synthesis at the ribosome level, and fluoroquinolones inhibit enzymes necessary for DNA replication. The misuse of antibiotics has led to the emergence and spread of resistant strains of bacteria, a problem recognized by the WHO as one of the serious threats to global health.', -12.061860799789429)]])
